# LifeOS — AI Rules & Domain Model

## Model Selection (follow this exactly)

| Task | Model | Reason |
|------|-------|--------|
| Classify user input → domain + fields | Haiku | Simple extraction, runs 50×/day |
| Generate morning briefing text | Haiku | Narrative from structured data |
| Extract time, date, recurrence from text | Haiku | Entity extraction |
| Tag ideas, detect priority | Haiku | Classification |
| "What should I focus on today?" | Sonnet | Reasoning across many entries |
| Prioritize across domains | Sonnet | Nuanced judgment needed |
| AI chat conversation | Sonnet | Context + multi-turn reasoning |
| Anti-entropy review | Sonnet | Behavior pattern analysis |

**Rule: never call Sonnet for what Haiku can do. Cost difference is ~10×.**
**Rule: Sonnet only fires on explicit user request, never proactively.**

