## Spaced Repetition (lib/spaced-repetition.ts)

Use SM-2 algorithm for learning goals. After each session log:
- If quality ≥ 3 (reviewed well): increase interval
- If quality < 3 (forgot/struggled): reset interval to 1 day

```typescript
// Simplified SM-2
export function nextReviewDate(
  lastReviewedAt: Date,
  intervalDays: number,
  quality: 0 | 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5  // 0=blackout, 5=perfect
): Date {
  const newInterval = quality >= 3
    ? Math.round(intervalDays * 2.5)
    : 1
  const next = new Date(lastReviewedAt)
  next.setDate(next.getDate() + newInterval)
  return next
}
```

pg_cron runs nightly to check `last_reviewed_at + interval_days < now()` and
schedules a push notification for due learning items.

